english:
  title: At the Ujang Relay Station
  author: Choe Chiwon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    On the sandy shore I stand with horse, waiting for the returning boat.
    A stretch of misty waters—the sorrow of ten thousand ages.
    Only when mountains flatten to plains and waters run dry,
    Will parting finally cease in the human realm.
  footnotes:
    - Ujang Relay Station (芋江驛亭) was a stopping point along the communication routes of ancient Korea. This poem reflects on the nature of separation and impermanence through the lens of a traveler's moment of waiting.
